// This is the master list of which permissions exist.
// A single permission represents a set of actions a user can do.
// In general, a permissions should be added if there is a need 
// to have fine grained control over who can do the set of actions.

// Key questions to ask yourself before adding a permissions:
// 1. Will all users always have it, or can the service be open to everyone?
//    E.g. reading which notification methods exist is something all users should be able to do.
//    There is no need to have a permission for it since it will never be restricted. 
// 2. Can the authorizatin be inferred by another way?
//    E.g. a user should always be able to edit his own profile, no need for a permission to edit user profiles.
// 3. Does this really need to be a separate permission, or can it be covered by an existing one?
//    E.g. most of the time separate permissions for creating, updating and deleting a resource is
//    is not necessary as a "admin" and "read" permission cover all the use cases.

